# Unsupervised learning of donor phenotypes in ORCHID

This repository contains a cleaned notebook and Python script for unsupervised clustering analyses of ORCHID donor data.

## Summary
The project applies unsupervised learning to identify physiological donor phenotypes across donation scenarios and evaluate whether similar donor profiles experience different procurement outcomes, suggesting system-level variability beyond measurable physiology.

## Methods
- Python
- pandas, NumPy
- scikit-learn
- statsmodels
- UMAP

## Data access
The ORCHID dataset is not included here. Access requires credentialed access via PhysioNet and compliance with its data use conditions.

## Files
- `ORCHID_unsuperclustering_clean.ipynb`: cleaned notebook
- `ORCHID_unsuperclustering_clean.py`: editable Python script
